so madly in love with him?

432
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,160
I think that...

433
00:24:16,180 --> 00:24:17,640
he's totally my type.

434
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:20,600
And when I said
I wanted to win his heart,

435
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:22,600
he said...

436
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,680
Good luck with that, then.

437
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,240
Guys...

438
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,960
He gave me the chance himself.

439
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,680
I've gotta do my best.

440
00:24:44,140 --> 00:24:45,640
You're not just trying to win, are you?

441
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:49,120
Like, maybe he dared you or something.

442
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:52,920
Uh-uh, no.

443
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:55,000
I've never thought
about winning or losing.

444
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:56,780
I just know that I'm really into him,

445
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,040
and I don't wanna betray
my own feelings.

446
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,120
How so?

447
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,600
Let me put it this way.

448
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,000
Typically, a dog barks
at a plane, right?

449
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,120
But suddenly,

450
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:18,520
the plane opens the door
and lets the dog in.

451
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,400
Whoa, you really made us
get the picture.

452
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:29,040
What if you couldn't win him over?

453
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,480
I'll just cry.

454
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:33,280
So you'll cry and move on.

455
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,120
I'm not moving on.

456
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:34,840
- What?
- What?

457
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,360
Once I'm done crying,
I've gotta start over.

458
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,400
Shit...

459
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,680
Is there anything
that would make you back down?

460
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,040
Maybe if Qin told me
to stop pursuing him

461
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:47,760
and chased me out of his plane.

462
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,240
Or maybe...

463
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,880
if someone better came into his life.

464
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,200
Man, that's so freaking sick.

465
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,080
But I believe I'm the best.

466
00:26:04,280 --> 00:26:05,520
That's what makes you so unique.

467
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,240
Then, how about...

468
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:08,700
